    href="http:/www.w3.org/Consortium/Legal/copyright-documents"> <ins>W3C Document License </ins> </a> <ins>. See the </ins> <a
    href="http://www.w3.org/Consortium/Legal/ipr-notice#Copyright"> <ins>W3C Intellectual Rights Notice </ins> <del>You are granted a license to use, reproduce </del> and <ins>Legal Disclaimers </ins> </a> <ins>for additional information. </ins> <del>create derivative works of this document. </del> </p> </div> <hr> <h2 class="no-num no-toc" id="abstract"> Abstract </h2> <p> This specification defines Web Forms 2.0, an extension to the forms features found in HTML 4.01's Forms chapter and the corresponding DOM 2 HTML interfaces. Web Forms 2.0 applies to both HTML and XHTML user agents. It provides new strongly-typed input fields, new attributes for defining constraints, a repeating model for declarative repeating of form sections, new DOM interfaces, new DOM events for validation and dependency tracking, and XML submission and initialization of forms. It also standardises and codifies existing practice in areas that have not been previously documented, and clarifies some of the interactions of HTML form controls and CSS. <p> HTML4, XHTML1.1, and the DOM are thus extended in a manner that has a clear migration path from existing HTML forms, leveraging the knowledge authors have built up with their experience with HTML so far. <h2 class="no-num no-toc" id="status"> Status of this document </h2> <p> <em> <ins>This section describes the status of this document at the time of its publication. Other documents may supersede this document. </ins> </em> <p> This document is the result of a loose collaboration between interested parties in the context of the <a href="http://www.whatwg.org/"> Web Hypertext Application Technology Working Group </a> . <p> <del>This is the working copy of Web Forms 2.0. </del> If you wish to make comments regarding this document, please send them to <a href="mailto:whatwg@whatwg.org">  whatwg@whatwg.org </a> <ins>( </ins> <a
   href="http://www.whatwg.org/mailing-list"> <ins>archived public mailing list </ins> </a> <ins>). </ins> <p> <ins>This document has reached a stable stage. The following are the only known open issues with this document: </ins> <ul> <li> <ins>There </ins> <del>. All feedback </del> is <ins>some debate about whether the date and time </ins> <del>welcome. </del>  <del>Your </del> input <ins>types provide adequate fallback behaviour for legacy clients, in particular because the current model does not allow legacy clients to fall back on multiple controls or to show the expected date format. </ins> <li> <ins>There is some debate about whether the repetition model section should </ins> <del>will </del> be <ins>included or not. </ins> <li> <ins>This specification allows the children </ins> <del>taken into consideration. </del>    <del>Experimental implementations </del> of <code> <ins>form </ins> </code> <ins>elements to be inline-level if the </ins> <code> <ins>form </ins> </code> <ins>element is itself a descendant of a block-level element. However, there is some debate about whether </ins> this <ins>specification should exclude the </ins> <code> <ins>div </ins> </code> <ins>element from the list of allowed ancestors. </ins> <li> <ins>The model used by the </ins> <code> <a href="#validity"> <ins>validity </ins> </a> </code> <ins>DOM attribute is not very clean, and may deserve to be replaced with something that has been thought through with more care. </ins> <li> <ins>The version of the specification uses namespaces without defining actual literal strings to use for them and similarly avoids defining which DOCTYPE to use for documents that would comply </ins> <del>document are encouraged. Unless large problems are discovered, future changes </del> to this <ins>specification. </ins> <del>specification will be minor. </del>  This <ins>is intented to avoid the possibility </ins> <del>draft may contain namespaces </del> that <ins>authors begin to </ins> use the <ins>features described herein </ins>  <del>uuid: </del>  <del>URI scheme. These are temporary and will be changed </del> before <ins>they have been finalised. </ins> </ul> <del>this specification is ready to be implemented in consumer products. </del> <p> To find the latest version of this working draft, please follow the "Latest version" link above. <p> <ins>By publishing this document, W3C acknowledges that Opera Software ASA and the Mozilla Foundation have made a formal submission to W3C for discussion. Publication of this document by W3C indicates no endorsement of its content by W3C, nor that W3C has, is, or will be allocating any resources to the issues addressed by it. This document is not the product of a chartered W3C group, but is published as potential input to the </ins> <a
